         <abstract>
            <p>The author examines management of the aggregate cash position. The timing and amount of security purchases and sales are determined in the context of a two-level control-limit inventory model that employs a look-ahead heuristic. Maturity structure of transactions is determined by a smoothing heuristic that takes account of the trade-off between portfolio return and transaction cost savings.</p>
